<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>The Mattsowary Stacks</title>
  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      background-color: #014421; /* forest green */
      color: #f5f5f5;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    }

    h1, h2 {
      color: #7CFC00; /* bright green */
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    p {
      margin: 0.4rem 0;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 0.4rem 0 1rem;
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
    }

    .section {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
      padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .emoji-title {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Main blog intro -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="emoji-title">🌲 The Mattsowary Stacks</div>
      <h1>The Mattsowary Stacks</h1>
      <p>
        Welcome to The Mattsowary Stacks — a cosy corner of the internet where every book has a story,
        and every story has a journey.
      </p>
      <p>
        This blog follows the books discovered, rescued, adopted, or accidentally‑purchased‑in‑airport‑chaos
        by Mattsowary while travelling the world. From thrift shop treasures in tiny towns to unexpected finds
        in bustling cities, each post shares the adventure behind the book and why it earned a place on the stack.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- About the author -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="emoji-title">🧍‍♂️ About the Author</div>
      <h2>About the Author</h2>
      <p>
        Hi, I’m Matt — also known as Mattsowary.
      </p>
      <p>
        I travel, I collect, and I read (sometimes in that order). Wherever I go, I pick up a book to remember
        the place, the moment, or the chaos that led me there. Over time, this turned into a growing, slightly
        unhinged, very sentimental library of stories from around the world.
      </p>
      <p>
        This blog is my way of sharing those finds — the books, the memories, and the journey behind each one.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Schnauzer update -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="emoji-title">🐾 Schnauzer Update</div>
      <h2>Schnauzer Update</h2>
      <p>
        Welcome to the Schnauzer Update, the official news desk of the miniature schnauzer who supervises all
        book‑collecting activities.
      </p>
      <p>Expect occasional updates on:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>naps</li>
        <li>opinions on book covers</li>
        <li>travel adventures</li>
        <li>general schnauzer‑related chaos</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If a book makes it into the Stacks, it’s because the schnauzer approved it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="emoji-title">✉️ Get in Contact</div>
      <h2>Get in Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Got a book recommendation, a travel tip, or a schnauzer meme to share?
      </p>
      <p>
        Reach out anytime — I love hearing from fellow readers, travellers, and collectors.
      </p>
      <p>You can contact me through:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email</li>
        <li>Social links</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
